    <p class="indent">It was effective to engage our clinical team in prototyping exercises and design activities early so we could work a problem together. This would help us rapidly arrive at something feasible and reasonable given the challenges.</p>

    <p>Using what we learned about the feasibility, we would move quickly to put together an artifact that we could review and evaluate with customers and stakeholders. I developed good relationships with our account management team so I could quickly connect with customers to do a test or walk through of an artifact. For these customer meetings, I would use scenarios to come up with specific tasks or open ended questions. This early input provided tremendous value and yielded actionable outcomes quickly.</p>

