    <h4>Light Weight Documentation</h4>
    <p>Light weight documentation was my response to the timing and fluidity of ever-evolving requirements, designs, and data constraints. The last week of each sprint during my first six months on the job were filled with 12-hour days as I scrambled to codify each interaction, requirement, and detail of the user interface behaviors into a static document. I always got the requirements and documents &ldquo;done&quot;, but I was often discouraged when the off-shore team building the UI implemented it in a way I could have never imagined. This was a good lesson for me. I had been fully aware of the potential for this problem, yet still fell for immersing myself completely in the delivery of documents.</p>

